title: Border, 1810–25
description: Decorative architectural molding with a stylized classical motif. Simple acanthus leaf enclosed within tongue-like brackets which end in a rosette. Alternating, daisy-like flower and leaves. Dentilled edging. Printed in yellow, brown, tan, on orange ground.

tombstone.epitaph:
Border, 1810–25.
1810–25. Block-printed on handmade paper. Gift of Josephine Howell. 1972-42-18-a/d.
